Do you want to play this fun word game with me? After you watch the video, come up with your own word and put it in the comments! It’s addicting!

This word building activity will engage all your students while teaching prefixes, suffixes, spelling patterns, and new vocabulary! You can use this as a center or partner work, enrichment homework, whole or small group instruction, or even a five minute filler! node.text:
Student Lottery: Fun way for students to WIN random selection! Student Lottery can be used for mystery student selection, tasks or jobs, partner selection, desk checks, extra incentives, the possibilities are endless! I placed it on my desk this morning and my students waited with anticipation! The sound of the ping pong balls moving around adds instant excitement to student picking!

One tip: If you’re using the student lottery for academic questioning, pull the ball first, so you can differentiate your questions for each student after you pull it and know what type/level of difficulty they need.

All student names are on the ping pong balls, plus a few extra special ones. Ping pong balls from Dollar Tree and plastic fish bowl from Petco. I saw this brilliant idea from @fantasticallyfourth a few years ago and wanted to add it to our classroom again! #bts #bts21 #backtoschool #classroomideas

node.text:
Here are my students’ First Week Favorites. ❤️

Take some time and reflect at the end of each week/month to see what excited or engaged your students. This gives them a voice and makes them feel their opinions matter and are valued. It also gives you appreciation for all the hard work you put into their favorites! 🙌 (Took less than five minutes at the end of the day Friday.) We forgot a few things because we were in a hurry, but I’m glad they think they had a great week! ❤️

This is a great gauge for me to see what they liked or interested them. It helps me to plan future lessons, activities, or management tools in our classroom. I’m excited to see there was a nice balance of learning/fun favorites!

#firstweekofschool #backtoschool #teacherlife

Our Book Tasting was a huge success today! My students loved being introduced to new books through this experience! They explored new genres and styles of books they’ve never looked at before today! 😍🙌

They talked and discussed books, author’s craft, genres, importance of titles, hooks, readability, and so much more! I call this a big win! Let our reading lives in room 106 begin!

I like to have something on my students’ desks while we’re organizing supplies and trickling in on the first day. A word search with all their names is my favorite! 😍❤️ You can find free word search generators or create a 20x20 table in Word or PowerPoint. Fill in all your student names first, then fill in the rest with random letters. They love it! 
Side note…first day back is sooo exhausting!! 😝

There are so many ways to use the random selector! I plan on using it the first day to make sure students are listening to each other and build community the first day!

My students think the random student selector is the greatest thing EVER! They feel like they’re on a game show!

We use it to answer questions, vocabulary review, desk checks, group leaders, reflect on learning, prize winners, so many possibilities! 

I’ve used them for math lessons: prime/composite, factors/multiples, ways to make a number, etc. It’s the BEST number talks! 

I love them for a quick vocabulary review too! Synonyms, antonyms, parts of speech, use it in a sentence, etc.

Bring excitement to your digital learning or in person with these random student selectors!

I used these during distance learning too! It’s a great way to boost engagement! They love seeing their name on the screen!

I’ve included three options: names, photos, and numbers.

The link to these random student selectors is in my profile: bit.ly/randomselector #bts21 #firstdayofschool #bts #distancelearning #digitallearning

BEFORE & AFTER!!! After hundreds of hours this week from family and friends this classroom is ready to welcome my new fourth graders! Moving schools is no joke (especially when you have 25 years worth of stuff! 😝)! I’m so excited to work with all the amazing people at my new school!! They’ve all been so welcoming and supportive! ❤️ #classroommakeover #bts #classroomdecor #bts21 #bulletinboards #beforeandafter #beforeafter

node.text:
New space, new theme boards! I can’t wait to fill these up with all the books we share together! 

My theme boards are one of my most referenced spaces in our classroom! It’s amazing how quickly students catch on to theme and love discussing theme because of this visual! 

Here’s how it works:
We discuss theme for EVERY book we share together. The books may not end up on the same theme board each year because it depends on how convincing my students are with their evidence. After the possible themes are presented, our class votes on which one they felt was the strongest even though all the choices may be good, the one with the most votes wins.

•I don’t have a list of theme books because this resource can be used with any fictional text and many books have several possible themes. The students decide which theme is the strongest.

•Our theme boards only include books we share as a class, this way they can all provide evidence to support or refute a theme. 

This resource now includes a DIGITAL version. 🙌

Link to resource in my profile: bit.ly/themeboards #booklover #book #readingteacher #booktheme
